# Account Discovery Attack

## Objective
Simulated the first thing an attacker usually does after gaining access to a computer. The attacker asks questions like:
- Who am I?
- What users exist?
- Who is an administrator?
- What computer am I on?

This is called **Discovery**. Attackers don't immediately install malware or steal files — first, they learn about the system so they can plan their next move.

## Commands Run

| # | Command | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `whoami` | Tells the attacker which user account they're currently using |
| 2 | `hostname` | Identifies the machine name |
| 3 | `net user` | Lists all user accounts on the computer |
| 4 | `net localgroup administrators` | Lists accounts with the highest privileges |
| 5 | `ipconfig` | Reveals the network configuration |

## Investigation — Wazuh Alert

**Alert 1**
| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| agent.name | Windows11 |
| data.win.eventdata.commandLine | `"C:\WINDOWS\system32\net.exe" user` |
| rule.description | Discovery activity executed |

